Always take medication exactly as prescribed by your healthcare provider. Never adjust the dosage without consulting a medical professional first.
Before taking any new medicine, read the label carefully to understand the proper dosage and timing. Understanding the instructions is crucial for safety.
Do not share prescription drugs with others, even if they have similar symptoms. Each person requires a unique dosage tailored to their specific health needs.
Take antibiotics only for the full duration prescribed, even if you start feeling better. Stopping early can lead to antibiotic resistance and complications.
Keep a detailed list of all medications, including over-the-counter drugs and supplements. This helps prevent dangerous drug interactions.
Always inform your physician about all other medications and supplements you are currently taking. This ensures all potential interactions are properly assessed.
Store medicines in a cool, dry place, away from children and pets. Proper storage maintains effectiveness and prevents accidental ingestion.
