Common symptoms of the flu include fever and body aches. You might also experience a dry cough and general exhaustion.
Sudden onset of severe fatigue and muscle pain are classic signs of influenza. Keep an eye out for these symptoms.
A runny nose and sore throat often accompany the flu. These symptoms can make it difficult to speak or swallow.
High fever, sometimes reaching 103 degrees Fahrenheit, is a primary indicator of an influenza infection.
Headaches and body aches are very common when you have the flu. Rest is essential for recovery from these discomforts.
Sometimes, flu symptoms include a loss of appetite or digestive upset. Staying hydrated is crucial during this time.
Nasal congestion and sneezing are typical signs. These symptoms indicate inflammation in the upper respiratory tract.
