We observed the rapid transition from cool autumn rains to the dry, dusty heat characteristic of early spring.
Notice how the vibrant green of late spring slowly deepens into the rich, mature hues of midsummer.
The seasonal shift from winter to spring brings melting snow and the promise of warmer, longer daylight hours.
Transitional weather patterns often bring unpredictable mixes, like autumn storms followed by surprisingly warm spells.
The border between late summer and fall is signaled by the changing quality of the light and the ripening harvest.
Experiencing the transition from mild spring breezes to the intense heat of summer requires layering different types of clothing.
