Go straight down this avenue until you reach the main park. Then, take a right turn onto Elm Street.
From here, head straight for the intersection. You must then turn left onto the second street.
Walk right past the library, continuing straight for about half a mile. The destination will be on your right.
Take the first exit and continue straight. After the bridge, make a sharp left into the designated parking area.
When you see the fountain, turn right immediately. Keep walking straight until you pass the large oak tree.
After passing the gas station, turn left onto the smaller road. Walk straight until you see the bakery on your left.
Continue straight for two blocks, crossing the railway tracks. Then, take a right turn and walk until you find the main entrance.
When you arrive at the intersection, look for the large bank building; it will be directly across the street from you.
From the main intersection, take the second exit onto Elm Street. You will see the library immediately on your right.
At the intersection of Maple and Oak, turn right. Continue straight until you reach the third traffic signal.
Cross the busy intersection carefully, then proceed straight until the yellow brick wall becomes visible on your left.
Just before the intersection, signal to the right. Then, take the first available lane and continue for about a quarter mile.
When you get to the intersection, don't worry about the traffic. Just walk across and then head down the smaller side street.
If you cross the street, the bookstore is right across the street, next to the bakery.
Keep walking until you reach the main intersection. The pharmacy is directly across the street from the corner.
Turn right at the corner, and the park entrance will be visible across the street, past the red brick building.
Cross the main avenue, and you will find the large bank. It's situated directly across the street from this coffee shop.
Walk down this block until the traffic lights. After the lights, the grocery store is conveniently located across the street.
You'll pass a large fountain. The museum entrance is located across the street, just past the main plaza.
Go until you reach the busy intersection. The bus stop and the library are right across the street from each other.
If you head directly opposite the library, you will see a large green park and several picnic tables.
Across the street from the main library entrance, there is a bustling coffee shop and a small bookstore.
To find the nearest bank, proceed directly across the street, right opposite the public library building.
Just past the intersection, facing the library, the first major landmark you'll encounter is a pharmacy.
From the corner, walk straight until you reach the crosswalk; the opposite side houses a popular bakery.
Take a left turn and continue until you see the large plaza; the library is directly across from it.
Look directly across the busy road from the library; a row of brightly colored restaurants occupies that space.
The subway station is situated exactly opposite the library, making it very easy to access from either side.
Follow this road until you reach the main highway access point. The next step is to proceed directly through the long, covered tunnel.
From the roundabout, take the third exit onto the main artery. You must keep going straight and go through the tunnel to reach the city center.
Walk until the road narrows considerably. Look for the signs pointing toward the tunnel; you'll need to go through it next.
Head down this street until you encounter the underpass structure. Please go through the tunnel carefully, watching for any slowdowns.
After passing the bridge, the road dips down. You should continue straight and go through the tunnel until you exit into open air.
Take the ramp down and merge onto the expressway. Keep following the signs until you reach the point where you must go through the underground tunnel.
Turn right onto the feeder road. The quickest way across the river is to proceed directly through the tunnel, which is just ahead.
To reach the library, you simply need to take the next exit after passing the gas station. It will be on your right.
From the main road, take the next exit and continue driving until you see the large oak tree. The entrance is just past it.
When you approach the overpass, take the next exit onto Elm Street. The park will be immediately visible right there.
Keep driving until the signs for the commercial district appear. Then, please take the next exit; the shops are directly across the street.
You should take the next exit and turn right onto the service road. The hotel entrance is located at the end of that lane.
