Responsible pet ownership involves routine vet check-ups and necessary vaccinations for all animals.
Training puppies and kittens teaches them appropriate behavior within the home environment.
Providing adequate shelter and a safe outdoor area is crucial for canine well-being.
Always keep your dog on a leash when walking in public areas for safety.
Cross streets carefully, ensuring both you and your dog are visible to drivers.
Teach your dog to walk politely and ignore distractions from other animals.
