Goats are durable livestock known for their milk and their ability to graze diverse terrains.
Donkeys and horses serve as working livestock, used for transportation and pulling heavy carts.
Rabbits, while sometimes considered pets, are also utilized as livestock for their meat and fur.
Buffalo and oxen are powerful draft livestock, traditionally used for plowing fields and heavy labor.
